{
  "stem": "10353.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we, of course, we were very knowledgeable about finally what happened with Hitler getting into power and his marching into to-- to Vienna, to Austria, to conquer Austria.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "First of all, he took the Saarbrucken-- that was his first move that he took away from France, the Saar territory, and which followed by the invasion of Vienna, which later followed the demands of the Sudetenland, you know.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish people felt very, very much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And now, having said that the greatest majority of the population there were Hungarians, they rooted for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were-- but we were in trepidation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew what-- what was following.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so when they marched into Czechoslovakia, and they occupied the Sudetenland, we saw that the noose is gettin' tighter and tighter.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [BACKGROUND NOISE] We, of course, we were very well-aware of what happened-- the Sudetenland was decided at Munich.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we knew the episode with Chamberlain, and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we also, which was followed up by Germany demanding the Port of Danzig in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And prior to that, they had occupied-- there is a small port in Lithuania or Latvia-- I don't remember exactly-- which was called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they occupied [NON-ENGLISH], which followed by the demand of Danzig.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Poland would not relent.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And France and Britain was supporting Poland by not acceding to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Daily.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On a daily basis.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Daily, and practically, that occupied our-- out entire life, the conversation of-- of the political, and the situation that was going on and how it's culminating.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Finally, in 19-- [SIGHS] 39, I remember, I had-- I had finished my Judaic studies.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In 1939, we saw how the wind is blowing.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
